---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'UK Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/united-kingdom/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Ireland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ireland' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'ukFit', header: 'UK Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£340-490/mo', ukFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£400-570/mo', ukFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£305-435/mo', ukFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£285-405/mo', ukFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'UK Private (BUPA UK)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '£150-400/mo', ukFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '£305-490', annual: '£3,660-5,880' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '£420-650', annual: '£5,040-7,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '£565-870', annual: '£6,780-10,440' },
  { category: 'NHS (Residents)', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Free at point of use' },
  { category: 'UK Private Health', monthly: '£150-400/mo', annual: '£1,800-4,800' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in United Kingdom 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in the UK. NHS healthcare, historic sites, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in the United Kingdom"
  subheadline="The UK offers the NHS, rich history, English language, and familiar culture—home base for British expats returning and destination for Anglophiles worldwide."
  heroImage="/images/countries/united-kingdom-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose the UK</h2>
  <p>
    The UK offers the NHS (free healthcare for residents), rich history, English language, and familiar Western culture. For British expats returning home or Americans seeking English-speaking Europe, the UK is a natural choice despite weather and cost concerns.
  </p>

  <p>
    London offers cosmopolitan living at premium cost. Southwest England (Devon, Cornwall) attracts retirees. The Cotswolds provides quintessential English countryside. Edinburgh offers Scottish culture and beauty. Each region has distinct character and cost profile.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> NHS universal; private available</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> £2,000-4,500/month (~$2,500-5,700); high, varies by region</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mild; rainy; rarely extreme</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Historic; traditional; multicultural</li>
      <li><strong>Post-Brexit:</strong> New visa rules for non-UK/Irish</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">UK Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    The UK has the NHS—free at point of use for residents. Comprehensive coverage for GP visits, hospitals, procedures, prescriptions (small charge). Quality is good though wait times exist. NHS Trusts nationwide provide accessible care. Private sector offers faster access for those who can pay.
  </p>

  <p>
    Residents access NHS after establishing "ordinary residence." Private insurance provides faster access to specialists and procedures. For non-residents, international insurance or NHS surcharge payment required. NHS quality is good; private offers speed.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">NHS Access</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      NHS is free for "ordinary residents"—those lawfully and permanently in UK. Visitors may face charges or need insurance. Immigration Health Surcharge (IHS) applies to many visa holders. Private insurance provides faster elective access and avoids NHS wait times.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Post-Brexit UK visa rules apply to non-UK/Irish citizens:
  </p>

  <h3>Family Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For partners/parents of British citizens/settled persons. Income requirement applies. Leads to settlement after 5 years.
  </p>

  <h3>Skilled Worker Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For sponsored employment. Not typically retirement option but some professionals may qualify.
  </p>

  <h3>Innovator Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For entrepreneurs with innovative business idea. Endorsed route. May suit some retirees with business plans.
  </p>

  <h3>Standard Visitor</h3>
  <p>
    Up to 6 months. Not for long-term retirement. Cannot access NHS.
  </p>

  <h3>Irish Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Common Travel Area allows Irish citizens to live and work freely in UK.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for the UK:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa holders:</strong> Immigration Health Surcharge (IHS) provides NHS access</li>
    <li><strong>Ordinary residents:</strong> NHS free; private optional</li>
    <li><strong>Visitors:</strong> International/travel insurance essential</li>
    <li><strong>Private:</strong> For faster access to specialists/procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for UK</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      For residents: NHS provides comprehensive base; private insurance for faster access to elective procedures. For visa holders: IHS gives NHS access. For visitors: international insurance essential. Private covers speed and choice; NHS provides safety net.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in the UK, coverage depends on residency status:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for UK</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong UK network, international coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> UK-headquartered, excellent local network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA UK:</strong> Domestic private option for residents</li>
    <li><strong>NHS:</strong> Free comprehensive coverage for residents</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage options for UK healthcare access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for UK vary by status and coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NHS reliance:</strong> For residents, NHS covers most needs free</li>
    <li><strong>Private for surgery only:</strong> Cover elective procedures; use NHS otherwise</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> Reduces private premiums significantly</li>
    <li><strong>Outside London:</strong> Much lower living costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Returning Brit, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,800/month pension. Returning after overseas career. Cotswolds.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> NHS access + BUPA UK private for faster elective.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA UK ~£250/month. Coming home; dual coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Anglophile, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,000/month pension. Family visa via British spouse. London area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> IHS provides NHS + Cigna Global for comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> IHS ~£624/year + Cigna ~£450/month. Historic living; dual coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Irish Cross-border, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,500/month pension. Irish citizen moving to Northern Ireland.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Common Travel Area access. NHS Northern Ireland.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> NHS free; optional private ~£200/month. Cross-border ease.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the NHS really free?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For ordinary residents, yes—free at point of use. Funded by taxation. Small prescription charges apply (free for 60+). Dental has charges. Visitors face charges or need insurance. Quality is good; wait times for non-urgent care exist.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Has Brexit affected retirement in UK?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—EU/EEA citizens no longer have automatic right to live in UK. Now need visa like other nationalities. Those already settled may have pre-settled/settled status. New arrivals face standard immigration requirements.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is private insurance worth it in UK?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Depends on priorities—NHS provides good care but with wait times. Private insurance provides faster access to specialists, shorter waits for elective surgery, choice of hospital. For hip replacements, cataracts, etc., private speeds access. Personal choice.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the UK affordable for retirement?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Varies hugely—London is very expensive; regions much more affordable. Southwest, Wales, Scotland, Northern England offer better value. Budget £2,000-4,000/month outside London for comfortable living. Healthcare being free helps affordability.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with UK coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with UK authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
